quran[51]{c,v,t}:
  26,1,Ta Seen Meem
  26,2,these are the verses of the Book that makes everything clear
  26,3,"Perhaps, [Prophet] you punish yourself with grief because they will not believe"
  26,4,"If We so will, We can send down from heaven a miracle that will force their necks to remain bowed in humility"
  26,5,"Whenever a new revelation comes to them from the Merciful-to-all, they turn away"
  26,6,"They have already denied the truth, but the news of what they used to ridicule will come back to [hunt] them"
  26,7,"Do not they see the earth, and how many kinds of noble pairs of plants, We have caused to grow in it"
  26,8,"There is a sign in this, but most of them will not believe"
  26,9,"Truly your Lord is the Almighty, the Merciful-to-all"
  26,10,"When your Lord called on Moses, [saying], \"Go to the unjust people"
  26,11,the people of Pharaoh. Will they not be mindful of Me
  26,12,"He said, \"My Lord, I fear that they will call me a liar"
  26,13,"and that my breast will tighten, and my tongue will be tied, so send for Aaron"
  26,14,"Besides, they have a charge against me, so I fear that they will kill me"
  26,15,"[God] said, \"No. Go both of you with Our signs; We are with you, listening"
  26,16,"Go to Pharaoh and say, \"We are messengers from the Lord of the worlds"
  26,17,let the Children of Israel go with us
  26,18,"[Pharaoh] said, \"Did we not raise you among us as a child, and did you not live among us for many years"
  26,19,"[Then] you committed that crime of yours, you were so ungrateful"
  26,20,"[Moses] said, \"At the time I did it, I was of the misguided"
  26,21,So I fled from you because I feared you. Then my Lord gave me wisdom and made me one of the Messengers
  26,22,"As for that favor of which you remind me, was it not because you enslaved the Children of Israel"
  26,23,"Pharaoh said, \"But what is the Lord of the worlds"
  26,24,"He said, \"The Lord of the heavens and earth and all that is between them, if you only knew"
  26,25,"[Pharaoh] said to those around him, \"Do you hear [what he said]"
  26,26,"[Moses went on], \"Your Lord and the Lord of your forefathers"
  26,27,"[Pharaoh] said, \"This messenger who has been sent to you is really mad"
  26,28,"[Moses] said, \"Lord of the east and the west and that between them, if you [would just use your] reason"
  26,29,"[Pharaoh] said, \"If you take a god other than me, I will surely imprison you"
  26,30,"[Moses] said, \"Even if I show you undeniable proof"
  26,31,"[Pharaoh] said, \"Bring it, then, if you are telling the truth"
  26,32,"So [Moses] threw down his staff; and behold, it was an undeniable snake"
  26,33,"Then he drew out his hand, and-behold- it was [shining] white for all to see"
  26,34,"[Pharaoh] said to the notables around him, \"This is a skilled magician"
  26,35,"He wants to drive you out of your land with his magic, so what do you recommend"
  26,36,"They said, \"Let him and his brother wait for a while, and [meanwhile] send marshals to all the cities"
  26,37,to bring every skilled magician
  26,38,So the magicians were assembled at the appointed time on the appointed day
  26,39,"It was said to the People, \"Have you assembled"
  26,40,so that we might follow the magicians if they win
  26,41,"When the magicians arrived, they said to Pharaoh, \"Is there a reward for us if we win"
  26,42,"He said, \"Yes. You will be in my inner circle"
  26,43,"Moses said to them, \"Throw whatever you will throw"
  26,44,"So they threw their ropes and their staffs, and said, \"By the might of Pharaoh, We will surely win"
  26,45,"Then Moses threw down his staff, and it devoured their deceptions"
  26,46,"And down fell the magicians in prostration [to God]"
  26,47,"saying, \"We believe in the Lord of the Worlds"
  26,48,the Lord of Moses and Aaron
  26,49,"[Pharaoh] said, \"How dare you believe in Him before I have given you permission? He [Moses] must be your leader who has taught you magic. But soon you will know. I will cut off your hands and feet on opposite sides, and I will crucify all of you"
  26,50,"They said, \"We do not care! We will be returning to our Lord"
  26,51,"We hope that our Lord will forgive us our sins, because we were the first believers"